OL,3,CHigh Court told Matt Hancock libelled
OL,4,CAndrew Bridgen to 'devastating extent'
OL,6,FAt a hearing today (12th June), Mrs
OL,7,FJustice Collins Rice was asked to
OL,8,Fdecide several preliminary issues in
OL,9,Fthe case, including the "natural and
OL,10,Fordinary" meaning of Mr Hancock's post
OL,11,Fand whether it was a statement of fact
OL,12,For opinion.
OL,14,FChristopher Newman, representing Mr
OL,15,FBridgen, said the nature of the
OL,16,Fallegations reduced the standing of
OL,17,Fhis client in the eyes of the public
OL,18,Fto a "devastating extent".
