OL,3,CHigh Court told Matt Hancock libelled
OL,4,CAndrew Bridgen to 'devastating extent'
OL,6,FHe said: "The claimant contends that
OL,7,Fthe statement impugns his character or
OL,8,Fbelief system, 'an antisemite',
OL,9,Fwhereas the defendant contends that it
OL,10,Fconcerns only the qualities of what he
OL,11,Fhas said, 'disseminated views that
OL,12,Fwere antisemitic in nature'."
OL,14,FHe continued: "The political context
OL,15,Fof the statement is highly
OL,16,Fsignificant. The reasonable reader
OL,17,Fwill have appreciated that it was one
OL,18,FMP criticising a statement made by
OL,19,Fanother MP on a matter of political
OL,20,Fcontroversy.
